question: Matt has 95 hectares of strawberry field. There are 60 strawberrys per hectare. Matt can harvest his strawberrys every 3 months. How many strawberrys can Matt harvest within a year?
answer:
Matt has 60*95= <<60*95=5700>>5700 strawberrys on his field.
Matt can harvest his strawberrys 12 / 3 = <<12/3=4>>4 times per year
Therefore Matt can harvest 5700*4 = <<5700*4=22,800>>22,800 strawberrys per year.
#### 22,800
